&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cards team at Stripe is responsible for the infrastructure, user facing features, and business of accepting credit, debit, and pre-paid card payments. Delivering the best offering for processing credit, debit, and prepaid cards is critical to Stripe’s mission, given the central role card payments play in internet commerce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager for Cards Pricing at Stripe, you’ll be responsible for pricing Card payment products worldwide. Everyday - You’ll balance the needs of our customers and competitive landscape, while helping Stripe maintain its margins.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Stripe, Product Managers help build innovative payments products for our customers. Product development is an extremely collaborative effort between engineering, design, analytics, operations and customer-facing teams. You’d be joining a team of experienced Product Managers who have a track record of successfully building large-scale business and consumer products that are collectively impacting millions of users around the world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This strategically critical role offers significant exposure to Stripe&#39;s leadership as you will drive initiatives to create observability into Stripe’s margins and revenue realization on Cards, define pricing principles and streamline pricing operations. This is a highly cross-functional role - On a day to day basis, you will spend your time between meeting customers (both internal and external), and working with your engineering, operations, analytics, network partnership, pricing, finance and GTM counterparts. You will use the voice of the customers, go deep into data, and leverage ML/GenAI as you define pricing strategies and build margin and revenue monitoring and alerting systems. Your decisions will have millions of dollars of impact to Stripe’s business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Card pricing - defining pricing principles, driving pricing decisions and operationalizing those decisions working with pricing, finance, marketing and GTM teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To effectively set prices, you’ll work with engineering and data science to build observability into current pricing, margin and revenue realization. You’ll drive insights, and translate those into pricing recommendations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll define processes for competitive analysis and regular pricing audits. Over time, you’ll work with engineering and data science to automate pricing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’ll work backwards from customers, and keep a keen eye on competitors to identify new pricing models. You’ll build the business case, find ways to test, and if validated, build out the new pricing models.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This is a highly cross-functional role. On a daily basis, you’ll work with various stakeholders across the organization, including Engineering, Design, Data Science, GTM, Pricing, Marketing, PMs and Operations to drive flawless execution on product and pricing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ultimately, you’ll emerge as the expert and primary point of contact across all of Stripe for everything related to card pricing and GTM processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings 5+ years of experience in a product role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings 3+ years of experience in Pricing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively collaborate with engineering, product, data science, and cross-functional teams. Experience working with go-to-market teams in a B2B sales environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to deeply analyze data, derive insights, and make data-driven decisions. Proven track record of instrumenting and measuring product initiatives, including those with less obvious metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has strong written and verbal communication skills with a talent for simplifying complex concepts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has been successful in delivering continuous product improvement as well as 0 -&amp;gt;1 launches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brings ownership mindset and persistence to work on whatever it takes to ensure that your product is successful&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to deliver high-impact presentations to executive audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Has the ability to thrive with a high level of autonomy and responsibility&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Payments, working with Card Networks or Banking partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with ML, data science and data analyst teams. SQL proficiency will help.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing and growing platform products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience overseeing operational processes or managing operational teams&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Who we are&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About Stripe&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;About the team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cards team at Stripe is responsible for the infrastructure, user facing features, and business of accepting credit, debit, and pre-paid card payments. Delivering the best offering for processing credit, debit, and prepaid cards is critical to Stripe’s mission, given the central role card payments play in internet commerce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a product manager to drive our Stripe Cards Vault product efforts and strategy globally. Specifically, this product manager will own a critical card payments performance product that is used by millions of Stripe customers to tokenize, manage and update their card credentials. Our Cards Vault is paramount to our customers as it directly helps grow their revenue and reduce user churn thanks to secure, always up to date credentials for returning customers. In this role, you will own the roadmap and business impact of one Stripe’s core business critical products. You will engage with key ecosystem partners such as card networks, partner with an experienced Engineering lead and collaborate with GTM teams to ensure Stripe’s card updater and tokenization solutions are defining the industry best-in-class standard.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the long-term vision and strategy for Stripe’s Card updater capabilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a holistic strategy for Stripe’s tokenization solutions to support our multiprocessor strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage with users to deeply understand their needs, associated pain points and opportunitiesBuild and launch new capabilities that bring significant value to customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set priorities and execution roadmap for the team, innovate with your engineering team to identify novel opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with Finance to maintain product P&amp;amp;L and identify opportunities for growth and improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with other stakeholders across Stripe such as Data Science, Product Marketing, Payments Strategists and GTM teams to deliver high quality product experience to users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Product experience: 5+ years of relevant experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business acumen: You enjoy digging into the details of how a business works, identifying how to make it better, and building product solutions that deliver business value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analytical horsepower: You dig deep into the data, think from first principles, and deliver the right results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Results-oriented: You enjoy doing whatever it takes to execute on complex projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Customer and Partner facing experience: You’re comfortable in front of customers or third-party collaborators, and have experience navigating customer conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational savvy: You are strong operationally, capable of designing and driving a cross-functional team and process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Crisp communicator: High attention to detail including precise and effective communications, including with external customers/partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in or knowledge of card based payments, or payments in general&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SQL or a willingness/aptitude to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with products with complex technical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in external facing role (sales, partnerships) and business negotiation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Commerce Systems&lt;/strong&gt; team is at the literal nexus of Stripe’s expansion to a full-fledged Financial Services infrastructure platform. We own the internal revenue engine that enables every product team at Stripe to monetize their offerings, manage fees, and create complex commercial constructs. You will join a high-leverage 110-person organization, partnering with &lt;strong&gt;10–20 engineers&lt;/strong&gt; to harmonize disparate systems—from billing to financial data warehouses—into a single, elegant interaction surface.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the PM for Commerce Systems, you will be the architect of the &#39;engine room&#39; of Stripe’s revenue. You will be responsible for building the unified control planes that harmonize Stripe’s internal billing, seller systems, and financial data warehouses into a single, high-leverage interaction surface. In this role, your mission is to eliminate integration friction for internal product teams, allowing them to ship faster, while ensuring our merchants receive the world-class fee transparency and reconciliation tools they need to run their businesses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harmonize Infrastructure:&lt;/strong&gt; Build the &quot;control planes&quot; that unify seller systems, user billing, and financial data warehouses to reduce integration friction for product teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect for Velocity:&lt;/strong&gt; Drastically reduce the time-to-market for new Stripe products by streamlining monetization workflows and core underlying capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Strategy:&lt;/strong&gt; Articulate the product vision for our revenue platform, developing annual and quarterly plans that align with Stripe’s rapid expansion into AI and new financial services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Navigate Complexity:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a leader and change agent, thriving in &quot;chaos&quot; to turn operational noise into a clear engineering roadmap.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner with engineering leaders to design ingestion, enrichment, and serving interfaces while acting as a thought partner for GTM, Finance, and Legal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7+ years of experience&lt;/strong&gt; as a Product Manager in technology companies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Backend Foundation:&lt;/strong&gt; Deep experience with large-scale backend systems and an API-first mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Platform Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven track record building platform infrastructure that serves the needs of multiple disparate stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to synthesize complex technical discussions and write succinctly for senior leadership. The ability to work cross functionally and speak multiple ‘languages’: you’re equally credible as a thought partner for Go-to-Market, Engineering, Finance or Legal leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Resilience:&lt;/strong&gt; Comfort dealing with many moving pieces and evolving legacy systems into their next generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Most importantly, we’re looking for great product managers who deeply understand their users, turn that into great plans, and make those plans happen. Even if you don’t have all the experience above we’d encourage you to apply if this role excites you&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Fintech or at a Hyperscaler Cloud Infra provider (e.g., AWS, GCP, Azure).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing technical software products from infancy to scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A background in designing and building multi-product platforms or complex billing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Compliance organization is responsible for building the most trustworthy network in the financial ecosystem by safely and efficiently managing complex global regulatory and partner obligations. We are executing a multi-year, strategic investment to embed automation, self-service, and AI across all workflows, ensuring our platform can scale reliably and safely to meet all future global demands.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Product Manager who will own a part of the compliance platform and help us transform how we execute large-scale, ongoing compliance requirements globally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Manager for the Compliance Platform, you will be responsible for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Owning the core compliance control plane:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and deliver the unified API and self-service platform that serves as the single source of truth for all large-scale, ongoing compliance program execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Driving&amp;nbsp; operational autonomy and safety:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the strategic shift to enable non-engineering teams to autonomously manage global compliance programs end-to-end, building in guardrails and intelligence to eliminate operational errors and achieve zero unintended business disruptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maximizing engineering and data leverage:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure the platform&#39;s architecture and data model are highly accurate and extensible, shifting the engineering focus from manual execution and data cleanup to platform innovation and automation across all operational workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years in Product Management, specifically in shipping large-scale, complex, and technical platform or infrastructure products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience leading ambitious, ambiguous 0-to-1 projects that require significant cross-functional alignment and organizational change.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of API design and data modeling principles, with a track record of building reusable, high-leverage components&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication, influence, and stakeholder management skills to negotiate timelines and align roadmaps across multiple organizations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Data-driven approach to product management, with experience defining and tracking metrics related to operational efficiency, platform health, and system accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building internal tooling or &quot;platform-as-a-service&quot; offerings that successfully centralize and automate decentralized operational workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background working on products that utilize Machine Learning or AI to automate complex decision-making processes or generate optimized operational plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Stripe&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stripe is a financial infrastructure platform for businesses. Millions of companies—from the world’s largest enterprises to the most ambitious startups—use Stripe to accept payments, grow their revenue, and accelerate new business opportunities. Our mission is to increase the GDP of the internet, and we have a staggering amount of work ahead. That means you have an unprecedented opportunity to put the global economy within everyone’s reach while doing the most important work of your career.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a platform company powering businesses all over the world, Stripe processes payments, runs marketplaces, detects fraud, helps entrepreneurs start an internet business from anywhere in the world, builds world-class APIs, and more. As we aspire to be the world&#39;s financial infrastructure, we have to internally create a finance infrastructure that can scale to our aspirations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The FinSys team builds the financial infrastructure that enables Stripe to make data driven decisions while operating with the rigor of a public company - improving financial decision making, ensuring regulatory compliance, and driving operational efficiency through automation. The Finsys Business insights team is responsible for building products that help Stripe make better financial decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Product Manager for the Finsys team, you will be a driving force behind the creation and development of our&amp;nbsp; Financial Business Insights products. Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conducting in-depth market research to identify unmet customer needs and emerging market trends&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional teams, including engineering, design, data science, finance, accounting etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Defining and executing product roadmaps, including setting priorities, managing resources, and ensuring timely delivery of new features and functionality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously gathering customer feedback, analyzing performance data, and iterating on product designs to optimize the user experience and drive impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Championing the product vision and garnering buy-in from key stakeholders, including executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and executing roll out strategies to ensure successful product launches and ongoing customer adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying and mitigating potential risks and challenges throughout the product development process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for someone who meets the minimum requirements to be considered for the role. If you meet these requirements, you are encouraged to apply. The preferred qualifications are a bonus, not a requirement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of product management experience, with a focus on new product development and incubation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to work cross-functionally and collaborate effectively with engineering, design, marketing, and other teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with the ability to make data-driven decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to articulate complex ideas to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An entrepreneurial mindset and a willingness to take on ambiguous, high-impact projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
